@ingvar1995 friend search? what do you mean? Each friend is identified by one single toxid.

@zoff99  completely misunderstanding, for the key pairs, in tox, there are the key pair identifies the user (toxid), dht key pair, session key pairs, and many random key pairs. 

The proposal says same key pair used to identify the user(toxid), but different dht key pairs for different devices, not to mention each device uses different session key pairs. For communication, different devices use different key pairs, they never use the same key pair for communication. But since they all attached to the same toxid! The purpose of the proposal is to map different dht key pairs to the same toxid. Yes, there is one same private key for the toxid! One same secret for user authentication.
If the device compromised, then yes, it affects all devices since all devices are equal.

Unless you define master & slave devices, you have the same situation no matter what kind of approach. The same user have to be authenticated on multiple devices. How to identify/authenticate the user? My proposal is to use the same toxid, so same private key pair. Though it is rarely used, it is used only to authenticated the user locally and remotely. Communications(Net_Crypto) are using session key pair, though its setup is based on dht key pair, and involves toxid key pair as for remote friend authentication.

@zoff99 the modification in this PR by now, does not affect old versions. but only to prevent the leaking of toxid(pkTarget). It was unnecessary leaking to require pkPacket == pkTarget. We can let pkPacket to be random for both cases (setup & query). 

I mean for both cases(setup & query), in onion_client.c, in the function client_send_announce_request, when calling create_announce_request, the temp key pair could be used, rather than use toxid key pair for setup. toxid pk is delivered as pkTarget, it is unnecessary to leak it as pkPacket.

Though we should not stop leaking of toxid key pair right now before this PR is accepted and spread over the network. Stop leaking will not be compatible with the old version since old version requires this leaking. Only after this PR has been accepted and spread over the network, we can stop leaking of toxid pk.

@ingvar1995 could you please write 2 more sentences. what you just said is difficult to understand. In the function client_send_announce_request, when num==0, it is the case for setup, when num!=0, it is the query. 

int create_announce_request(uint8_t *packet, uint16_t max_packet_length, 
  const uint8_t *dest_client_id,   //the pk of middle man
  const uint8_t *public_key, //pkPacket, 
  const uint8_t *secret_key, //to generate shared key with the middle man
  const uint8_t *ping_id, 
  const uint8_t *client_id, //pkTarget, to specify the forward target of the forward mechanism 
  const uint8_t *data_public_key, //to specify the pkData, to be used for anyone to send message to the target
  uint64_t sendback_data //the request ID
)

The real parameter is pingid & pkData.
For setup case, twice, 1st time pingid=0, pkData!=0, 2nd time pingid!=0, pkData!=0.
For query case, pingid=0, pkData=0.

for setup case, when the middle man received it, an Onion_Announce_Entry is created. 
for query case, Onion_Announce_Entry will be searched against its public_key(pkTarget). 

@ingvar1995 what do you mean? and do you have the right to do review and merge this PR?
